  <section class="moat-section">
    <div class="moat-inner">
      <h2>The Aivyx Advantage</h2>
      <p class="moat-subtitle">Four capabilities no other platform combines</p>
      <div class="moat-grid">
        <div class="moat-card">
          <div class="moat-icon">🔐</div>
          <h3>Privacy-First Encryption</h3>
          <p>ChaCha20Poly1305 at rest, per-purpose HKDF keys, passphrase never stored.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="moat-card">
          <div class="moat-icon">🛡️</div>
          <h3>Capability Attenuation</h3>
          <p>Type-system enforced permissions — agents can only use their permitted tools.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="moat-card">
          <div class="moat-icon">📋</div>
          <h3>HMAC Audit Chain</h3>
          <p>Tamper-proof, cryptographically verifiable log of every agent action.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="moat-card">
          <div class="moat-icon">🌐</div>
          <h3>Agent Federation</h3>
          <p>Ed25519-verified cross-instance collaboration with trust policies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="positioning">
    <div class="positioning-inner">
      <div class="position-card">
        <h3>vs ChatGPT & Claude</h3>
        <p>Powerful but cloud-only — your data lives on their servers. Aivyx runs on <strong>your machine</strong>, encrypts everything, and gives you a verifiable audit trail. Use the same models with Aivyx and keep your data under your control.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="position-card">
        <h3>vs LangGraph, AutoGen & CrewAI</h3>
        <p>Python-based agent frameworks without encryption, audit, or local-first architecture. Aivyx is a <strong>production-ready platform</strong> written in Rust with privacy, security, and user-owned data at its core.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="position-card">
        <h3>vs Ollama + Open WebUI</h3>
        <p>A local chat interface. Aivyx is a local <strong>agent platform</strong> — persistent memory, 46 tools, 22 skills, 9-agent teams, voice, MCP connectivity, and encryption at rest.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .page-hero p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .comparison-table-section {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }
  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .comparison-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .comparison-table th,
  .comparison-table td {
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .comparison-table th {
    background: rgba(232,168,73,0.08);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .comparison-table .feature-col {
    text-align: left;
    min-width: 180px;
  }
  .comparison-table td:first-child {
    text-align: left;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .highlight-col {
    background: rgba(232,168,73,0.06) !important;
  }
  .comparison-table th.highlight-col {
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .section-header td {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-align: left !important;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  }
  .yes { color: #4ade80; font-weight: 700; }
  .no { color: #666; }
  .partial { color: #facc15; }
  small { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 400; }

  .moat-section {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .moat-inner {
    text-align: center;
  }
  .moat-inner h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .moat-subtitle {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .moat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .moat-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: left;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .moat-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .moat-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .moat-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .moat-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .positioning {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .positioning-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .position-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .position-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .position-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .position-card strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
